# Context7 + Vercel Defaults

- For framework/library questions, dependency upgrades, and API usage details, query `user-context7` first for up-to-date docs and examples.
- Treat Context7 as the source of truth for version-sensitive behavior (especially Next.js, React, Vercel platform APIs, and migration guidance).
- For React/Next.js implementation work, apply relevant Vercel-focused skills:
  - `vercel-react-best-practices` for performance and code quality
  - `next-best-practices` for App Router/RSC/data patterns
  - `next-cache-components` for Next.js 16 caching/PPR patterns
  - `next-upgrade` for version migrations
- For Vercel deploy requests, use `vercel-deploy` and default to preview deployments unless production is explicitly requested.
- If Context7 docs conflict with stale local guidance, prefer Context7 and update project docs/rules to match.
